<div class="m-4">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Welcome to MRDBID!</h1>

  <p class="p-mrdbid-orange">
    First time here? You may wish to begin with <a href="/articles/big-detour-mrbid-exd" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">The Big Detour to MRDBID (and to EXD)</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="my-4 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Research & Documentation</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-1">
      <li>
        <%= link_to "Mycology Articles", articles_path(subject: "Mycology"), class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline" %> -
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-600">Identification challenges, taxonomic issues, and research notes</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <%= link_to "All Articles", articles_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline" %> -
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-600">Browse all documentation and articles</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <ol>
    <li class="list-decimal list-inside text-sm text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-0.5"> Register to be able to store your fungi data. If you have experience in mycology and want to actively participate in editing and adding characters, email me after you register letting me know your experience level and/or area of expertise, and I will modify your account accordingly.</li>
    <li class="list-decimal list-inside text-sm text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-0.5"> Login to enter and access your data.</li>
    <li class="list-decimal list-inside text-sm text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-0.5"> Add, View, and manage your data.</li>
    <li class="list-decimal list-inside text-sm text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-0.5"> <strong>Optional:</strong> Participate in editing and adding characters that are required to completely describe your fungi data if you have the experience to do so.</li>
  </ol>

  <p class="p-mrdbid">To work on "Mushrooms" and other fungi, after you log in, click on the Mushrooms button.</p>

  <p class="p-mrdbid"><span class="text-red-500">Notice: </span> <strong>There are <u>a lot</u> of characters to consider!</strong> Formatting them for the real world is one of the main goals and challenges for this website. This is a work in progress, and we are always looking for help to improve the accuracy and completeness of the data.</p>
</div>